Class QueryParams

    • com.simondata.pouroversql.clients.QueryParams
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InputParams

    public class QueryParams
extends java.lang.Object
implements InputParams

    QueryParams

    QueryParms are parameters that are passed at query-time. They control the actual querying mechanism, such as number of rows to retrieve at a time.
